President Obama has nominated Albert Nájera, William C. Sibert, and Myron M. Sutton to serve as U.S. Marshals. Albert Nájera is a former Chief of Police in Sacramento and has experience in anti-terrorism and emergency operations. William C. Sibert is a Detective with the St. Louis Police Department and has experience in surveillance, narcotics identification, and investigations. Myron M. Sutton is a Special Investigator with the Indiana, Illinois, Iowa Foundation for Fair Contracting and has served as Sheriff of Newton County, Indiana. These individuals have shown a commitment to public service and are being nominated to serve and protect the American people.